public Map<E,E[]> map()

Returns a new Map instance which will contain the first Column as key and all elements of each Row as array as map value.

The Map instance is not backed by the Table in any form, so any modifications to it will keep the Table unaffected and vice versa.

public Map<E,E> map(int columnIndexKey,

Description copied from interface: TableTransformer
Returns a new Map instance which will contain the Column element for the first column index as key and the element of the Column with the second column index as value array as map value.

The Map instance is not backed by the Table in any form, so any modifications to it will keep the Table unaffected and vice versa.
